    <string name="lbl_bg_work_notif_title">Background work notification</string>
    <string name="lbl_bg_work_notif_msg_part01">There was a change in Android Oreo and every background service has to show its notification now.</string>
    <string name="lbl_bg_work_notif_msg_part02">Our app needs to monitor screen on/off state in background to work reliably and with low battery footprint. This monitoring consumes virtually no battery but we still have to show a fixed notification. Otherwise system will kill our app.</string>
    <string name="lbl_bg_work_notif_msg_part03">Fortunately this notification can be turned off in notification settings.</string>
    <string name="lbl_bg_work_notif_msg_part04">Tap on [Notification settings] button bellow and you will be redirected to notification settings screen. Uncheck category notification called [Widget update service] to hide this notification.</string>

